subject: Masters Golf Tournament
lead_paragraph: Aaron Baddeley of Australia won the Australian Masters, defeating Daniel Chopra of Sweden on the fourth playoff hole in Melbourne.Baddeley and Chopra were tied at 13-under-par 275 after 72 holes. They each parred the 18th hole three more times before Baddeley holed a par putt from 10 feet and Chopra missed a 6-footer.
